<p>This accessibility statement explains how accessible Your Apprenticeship app is, what to do if you have difficulty
    using it, and how to report accessibility problems with the app. </p>
<p>This app is run by the Department for Education. We want as many people as possible to be able to use this app. For
    example, that means you should be able to: </p>
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
    <li>invert colours and adjust contrast levels</li>
    <li>increase the text size without the text truncating or overlapping</li>
    <li>navigate the app using Switch Access</li>
    <li>get around the app using Voice Access</li>
    <li>listen to the app using TalkBack</li>
    <li>We have also made the text in the app as simple as possible to understand</li>
    <li><a href="https://mcmw.abilitynet.org.uk/" class="govuk-link" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">AbilityNet (opens in
            a new tab)</a>
        has advice on
        making your device easier to use if you have a disability </li>
</ul>
